'''Viith Yalu''' was the [[Master Shaper]] sent by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] to command the [[Damutek]] facility on [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]] during their [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. The Wayland facility was one of several [[Shaper caste|Shaper]] projects looking for ways to understand [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and defeat the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], but Viith Yalu's most notable success came not through Shaper bioscience, but through making contact with [[Bey Gandan]], a Jedi prisoner who was sent to the system as a [[Slavery/Legends|slave]], and who seemed to have already been crazed with jealousy and hatred due to his comrade [[Klin-Fa Gi]]'s relationship with [[Yabeley]].<ref name="EOTV">"[[Emissary of the Void]]"</ref>

Willingly joining forces with the Yuuzhan Vong, Jedi Gandan allowed Viith Yalu to implant a [[villip]] in his brain, and conspired with him to serve as the invaders' agent in a plot to sabotage [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] production on [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]]. The bacta plot was foiled by [[Klin-Fa Gi]] and [[Uldir Lochett]].<ref name="EOTV" />

